is set in terms of econometric methods used leaving 43 high quality studies finally results are also shown separately for 13 randomized trials the estimated impacts on time in school and learning of most school and teacher characteristics are statistically insignificant especially when the evidence is limited to the high quality studies the few variables that do have significant effects eg availability of desks teacher knowledge of the subjects they teach and teacher absence are not particularly surprising and thus provide little guidance for future policies and programs download topics international resources efficiency hoover institution 434 galvez mall room 151 stanford university stanford ca 94305 6010 phone 650.736 0942 fax 650.723 1687 2012 hanushek net questions or comments member log in stanford university
